==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neptunian
<hw>Nep*tu"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Neptunius</ets> belonging to Neptune: cf. F.
<ets>neptunien</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the
ocean or sea.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Formed by water or aqueous
solution; <as>as, <ex>Neptunian</ex> rocks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Neptunian races</b></col> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>, <cd>the
Malay and Polynesian races.</cd> -- <col><b>Neptunian theory</b></col>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>the theory of Werner, which referred the
formation of all rocks and strata to the agency of water; -- opposed to
the <contr>Plutonic</contr> theory.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neptunist</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Neptunian</ent>⟦br⟧
